  "title": "Intraaortic balloon pump in patients with cardiogenic shock complicating myocardial infarction. A systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized trials",
  "abstract": "REVIEW ARTICLE Intraaortic balloon pump in patients with cardiogenic shock complicating myocardial infarction 181 however, its role in cardiogenic shock has been the subject of ongoing debate.The mechanism of action is related to the timing and frequency of balloon inflation and deflation.When the balloon inflates during diastole, blood is displaced into the proximal aorta driving blood into the coronary arteries.The effect Introduction Cardiogenic shock complicates approximately 7% to 10% of myocardial infarction (MI) events. 1 Despite the recent advances in the management of this condition, mortality remains high (40%-50%). 2,3Intraaortic balloon pump (IABP) counterpulsation is the most common mechanical hemodynamic assist device;",
